2 November 2014Government wishes to advise members of the media about planned media briefings scheduled for the week of 3to 9 November 2014. On Monday, 3 November at 09:00am, Minister of Social Development, Bathabile Dlamini will brief the media during the launch of the National Disability Rights Awareness Month. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (DOC), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.On Thursday, 6 November at 10:00am, Minister in the Presidency, Jeff Radebe will brief the media about the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting held on 05 November 2014. The Post Cabinet media briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (DoC), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.Additional to these media briefings there are a number of public events that will be attended by the various Ministers. The details of the events are posted on the respective government websites.All members of the media are advised that the media briefings are subject to change. However, the Department of Communications (DoC) will continue to update the media through advisories.Enquiries: Nebo Legoabe Cell: 082 453 2874Issued by Department of Communications